{
  "texts": [
    "As a consequence of being memory bound, the strong scaling has a different behavior for 2D and 3D setups.",
    "For the former (smaller) case there is an optimal subdomain size of ≈ 2000 grid points that allows fitting the data to the CPU memory with reasonable exchange load between subdomains.",
    "On the contrary, for the 3D setup one should keep the subdomains larger than 30x30x30 grid points to avoid high exchange overheads.",
    "In this case, the code can effectively run on several thousand CPUs.",
    "The code is still expanding with new features."
  ]
}